    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="607"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">750G.00/7–850: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d607fn1">Repeated to Vienna as 65, <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                            >USUN</gloss> as 35, London as 239, Paris as 232, and Rome as 193,
                        Belgrade as 39, Trieste as 20.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-14T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 14, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 74 Jul 8.<note n="2" xml:id="d607fn2"
                        >Not printed.</note> Dept concurs there is no need for formal reply to
                    second Sov note on Trieste.<note n="3" xml:id="d607fn3">See editorial note, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Secy’s statement Jul 12 press
                    conference re Aust Treaty Depty’s mtg<note n="4" xml:id="d607fn4">Documentation
                        regarding the position of the United States respecting the Austrian Treaty
                        meetings is scheduled for publication in volume <hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >iv</hi>.</note> said “Second note merely rpts <pb facs="1353" n="1329"
                        xml:id="pg_1329"/> unfounded allegations in Sov note on Apr 20.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d607fn5">See editorial note, <ref target="#pg_1317">p.
                        1317</ref>.</note> This Govt’s reply of Jun 16<note n="6" xml:id="d607fn6"
                        >See editorial note, <ref target="#pg_1325">p. 1325</ref>.</note> adequately
                    answered those allegations.”</p>
                <p>Dept has informed Brit and Fr Embs its views and understands from Fr Emb that Fr
                    Govt sees no need for reply.</p>
                <p>Dept believes that it wld be helpful in our relations with Ital, Yugo and Aust
                    Govts if, in informing them of our views as stated para 1 above, we cld also say
                    that our Amb Moscow has orally acknowledged receipt second Sov note on Trieste
                    and has said that since it adds nothing to their earlier note we have nothing to
                    add to ours of Jun 16. We are suggesting this course to Brit and Fr Embs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
